    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix uninitialized pointer access in textlist widget initialization\n\n### Summary\nThe textlist widget in the GUI tracer module was accessing uninitialized pointers during text addition operations. This caused sporadic crashes and memory corruption when viewing trace logs in the GUI.\n\nThe issue occurred because the text and color array pointers were not initialized to NULL when creating a new textlist widget, leading to undefined behavior when realloc was called on garbage pointer values.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/gui/textlist.c`: Added proper initialization of textlist widget fields in new_textlist function\n"
}